caller_intent: Rebecca is verifying coverage details for unscheduled farm personal property, confirming the removal of a policy location, and checking eligibility of auto policies for inclusion in an umbrella policy.
resolution_steps: Jeff confirmed that specified items (tractors, saddle) fall under coverage F and explained scheduling requirements for high-value equipment.
Jeff instructed Rebecca to submit an endorsement request to CL processing at WestfieldGRP.com to remove location two and livestock coverage.
Jeff clarified that only the existing farm policy is currently listed as an underlying coverage for the umbrella policy.
Jeff noted that commercial auto policies through Westfield are eligible for inclusion, but personal auto policies (Auto Owners, National General/Intagon) require further review.
knowledge_required: Understanding of insurance coverage types (F, D, umbrella)
Eligibility criteria for umbrella policy underlying coverages
summary: Rebecca confirmed coverage details for farm property, received instructions to remove a policy location via endorsement, and clarified umbrella policy eligibility. Jeff provided guidance on coverage limits, scheduling requirements, and underlying policy inclusion criteria.
